This class can be used to create network interface configuration files. If 
a new interface is defined on a system, or an existing interface is modified,
Puppet will ifdown/ifup that interface upon modification.

Usage:

  network::interface' { 'eth1':
    device    => 'eth1',              # required, no default
    hwaddr    => 'aa:bb:cc:dd:ee:ff', # required, no default
    ipaddr    => '1.2.3.4',           # required, no default
    netmask   => '5.6.7.8',           # required, no default
    gateway   => '9.10.11.12',        # optional, no default
    bootproto => 'static',            # optional, default = static
    ipv6init  => 'yes',               # optional, default = yes
    mtu       => '1500',              # optional, default = 1500
    onboot    => 'yes',               # optional, default = yes
  }
